Code and Output for Paul, et al, IJE

Agricultural paraquat dichloride use and Parkinsons disease in Californias Central Valley

# Source Code Notebook for Paul, et al, Agricultural paraquat dichloride use and Parkinsons disease in Californias Central Valley
# 
# Steps:  
#   
# * Data Visualization  
# +  Figure S1 and Figure 2
# * Exposure Assessment
# + 1974-index year
# + 1974-index year with 10y lag
# + 20y - 10y prior to index year
# + 10y prior to index year
# * Analysis by Exposure Time Windows
# + 1974-index year
# + 1974-index year with 10y lag
# + 20y - 10y prior to index year
# * Data Visualization  
# +  Figure 3 and Figure S2
# * Supplemental Analysis
# + 10y prior to index year


options(stringsAsFactors=F)

###################################################################################################
# Data Visualization

## Figure S1 and Figure 2

library(pacman)
pacman::p_load(ggplot2, ggpubr, dplyr, tibble, Hmisc, data.table, formattable, tidyr, tidyverse, broom, ggrepel, hrbrthemes, lme4, nlme, readxl, sjPlot, sjmisc, sjlabelled, epiDisplay, ggtext, glue, viridis)

#load data
load('PQ_C_all.RData')
load('PQ_R_all.RData')


#scatter plot of data
ps1.1<-ggplot(PQ_C_all, aes(Year, ChemPound_avg, colour = PD, group = PD)) +
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size=6), axis.text.x=element_text(angle=45,hjust=1))  + theme_minimal() + xlab('Year') + ylab('Pounds Paraquat Active Ingredient Applied Per Acre') + ggtitle('Occupational GRAPES') +
  theme(legend.position="none") + xlim(1974,2009) + geom_point(position = position_jitter(w = 0.25, h = 0))


ps1.2<-ggplot(PQ_R_all, aes(Year, ChemPound_avg, colour = PD, group = PD)) +
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size=6), axis.text.x=element_text(angle=45,hjust=1))  + theme_minimal() + xlab('Year') + ylab('Pounds Paraquat Active Ingredient Applied Per Acre') + ggtitle('Residential GRAPES')  +
  theme(legend.position="none")+ xlim(1974,2009) + geom_point(position = position_jitter(w = 0.25, h = 0))

#Supplemental Figure 1
ggarrange(ps1.1, ps1.2, ncol = 2)

#remove outliers
PQ_C_all <- PQ_C_all[PQ_C_all$ChemPound_avg < quantile(PQ_C_all$ChemPound_avg,0.99), ]
PQ_R_all <- PQ_R_all[PQ_R_all$ChemPound_avg < quantile(PQ_R_all$ChemPound_avg,0.99), ]

#create facet indicator
PQ_R_all$facet<-"1:Residential"
PQ_C_all$facet<-"2:Occupational"

#combine datasets, stack rows for long dataset with facet variable to indicate exposure location
PQ_RC_all<-rbind(PQ_R_all, PQ_C_all)

#plot lbs/applied per year
#average index year: 2006, so plot on x-axis to 2006.5

#scatter plot
PQ_RC_all$facet<-factor(PQ_RC_all$facet, labels=c('1:Residential'='Residence', '2:Occupational'="Workplace"))


p2.1<-ggplot(PQ_RC_all, aes(Year, ChemPound_avg, colour = PD, group = PD))  + geom_point(position = position_jitter(w = 0.25, h = 0)) +
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size=6), axis.text.x=element_text(angle=45,hjust=1))  + theme_minimal() + xlab('Year') + ylab('Pounds Paraquat Applied Per Acre') + ggtitle('Agriculturally Applied Paraquat Dichloride\n', subtitle='Scatter Plot of lbs applied per person per year') + 
  theme(legend.position="right") + xlim(1974,2006.5)+ expand_limits(y=0) + facet_wrap(~facet, ncol = 2, scales = 'free_y') + theme_ipsum(plot_title_size=22, subtitle_size = 16, subtitle_face = 'bold', strip_text_size = 16, axis_text_size = 13, axis_title_size = 14) + theme(plot.margin=unit(c(1,0.5,-0.25,0.5), 'lines'))

#loess
p2.2 <- ggplot(PQ_RC_all, aes(Year, ChemPound_avg, colour = PD, group = PD)) + geom_smooth(method='loess') +
  theme(axis.text=element_text(size=6), axis.text.x=element_text(angle=45,hjust=1))  + theme_minimal() + xlab('Year') + ylab('Pounds Paraquat Applied Per Acre') + ggtitle('',subtitle='\nLOESS local regression line') + 
  theme(legend.position="right") + xlim(1974,2006.5)+ expand_limits(y=0) + facet_wrap(~facet, ncol = 2, scales = 'free_y') + theme_ipsum(subtitle_size = 16, subtitle_face = 'bold', strip_text_size = 16, axis_text_size = 13, axis_title_size = 14) + theme(plot.margin=unit(c(-2,0.5,1,0.5), 'lines'))

#Figure 2
ggarrange(p2.1, p2.2, ncol = 1)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

###################################################################################################
# Exposure Assessment


#load covariate data
load('C_cov.RData')
load('R_cov.RData')

#merge index year to exposure data
PQ_C_all_2<-merge(PQ_C_all, C_cov[,c('PEGID','IndexYR10','IndexYR')], by='PEGID' )
PQ_R_all_2<-merge(PQ_R_all, R_cov[,c('PEGID','IndexYR10','IndexYR')], by='PEGID' )


###########################
###########################
###########################
###########################

## Exposure assessment: 1974-Index Year

###########################
###########################
#AVERAGE INTENSITY Exposure Assessment
###########################
###########################

#get average yearly PQ application within 500m of residence or workplace during time window

#include years prior to index year (PD diagnosis/interview) for each participant
PQ_C_all_74<-PQ_C_all_2[PQ_C_all_2$Year<PQ_C_all_2$IndexYR, ]
PQ_R_all_74<-PQ_R_all_2[PQ_R_all_2$Year<PQ_R_all_2$IndexYR, ]

#average the PQ ChemPound across years in the exposure window:
PQ_C_avg_74 <- PQ_C_all_74 %>%
  dplyr::group_by(PEGID) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(ChemPound_avg_74 = mean(ChemPound_avg))  

PQ_R_avg_74 <- PQ_R_all_74 %>%
  dplyr::group_by(PEGID) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(ChemPound_avg_74 = mean(ChemPound_avg))  

#combine with covariates
PQ_C_avg_74<-merge(PQ_C_avg_74, C_cov, by='PEGID')
PQ_R_avg_74<-merge(PQ_R_avg_74, R_cov, by='PEGID')

########################
#get average exposure assessment descriptives (for Table 2)

PQ_R_avg_74 %>% group_by(PD) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(count=n(), mean=mean(ChemPound_avg_74, na.rm=T), sd=sd(ChemPound_avg_74, na.rm=T))
## # A tibble: 2  4
##      PD count  mean    sd
##   <int> <int> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1     0   821 0.825  1.72
## 2     1   824 1.02   1.92
PQ_R_avg_74 %>% dplyr::summarise(IQR=IQR(ChemPound_avg_74, na.rm=T))
##         IQR
## 1 0.8984375
PQ_C_avg_74 %>% group_by(PD) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(count=n(), mean=mean(ChemPound_avg_74, na.rm=T), sd=sd(ChemPound_avg_74, na.rm=T))
## # A tibble: 2  4
##      PD count  mean    sd
##   <int> <int> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1     0   782 0.877  2.01
## 2     1   800 1.25   2.52
PQ_C_avg_74 %>% dplyr::summarise(IQR=IQR(ChemPound_avg_74, na.rm=T))
##         IQR
## 1 0.9327847
#######################
#scale ChemPound_avg_74, so OR per yearly average of 10 pounds per acre
PQ_C_avg_74$ChemPound_avg_74_10 <- scale(PQ_C_avg_74$ChemPound_avg_74, center = FALSE,
                                         scale = 10)
PQ_R_avg_74$ChemPound_avg_74_10 <- scale(PQ_R_avg_74$ChemPound_avg_74, center = FALSE,
                                         scale = 10)

#######################
#log transform exposure measure, offset by 1
PQ_C_avg_74$log_lbs_avg_74<-log(PQ_C_avg_74$ChemPound_avg_74 + 1)
PQ_R_avg_74$log_lbs_avg_74<-log(PQ_R_avg_74$ChemPound_avg_74 + 1)

PQ_R_avg_74 %>% group_by(PD) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(count=n(), mean=mean(log_lbs_avg_74, na.rm=T), sd=sd(log_lbs_avg_74, na.rm=T))
## # A tibble: 2  4
##      PD count  mean    sd
##   <int> <int> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1     0   821 0.385 0.563
## 2     1   824 0.456 0.619
PQ_R_avg_74 %>% dplyr::summarise(IQR=IQR(log_lbs_avg_74, na.rm=T))
##         IQR
## 1 0.6410312
PQ_C_avg_74 %>% group_by(PD) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(count=n(), mean=mean(log_lbs_avg_74, na.rm=T), sd=sd(log_lbs_avg_74, na.rm=T))
## # A tibble: 2  4
##      PD count  mean    sd
##   <int> <int> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1     0   782 0.374 0.598
## 2     1   800 0.489 0.693
PQ_C_avg_74 %>% dplyr::summarise(IQR=IQR(log_lbs_avg_74, na.rm=T))
##         IQR
## 1 0.6589606
###########################
###########################
#ANY APPLICATION Exposure Assessment
###########################
###########################

#any application exposure assessment 
PQ_C_avg_74$ever_74<-ifelse(PQ_C_avg_74$ChemPound_avg_74>0,1,0)
PQ_R_avg_74$ever_74<-ifelse(PQ_R_avg_74$ChemPound_avg_74>0,1,0)

########################
#frequency of any application (for Table 2 descriptives)
tabpct(PQ_R_avg_74$ever_74, PQ_R_avg_74$PD, decimal = 3, percent = "both",graph = F, las = 0, main = "auto", xlab = "auto", ylab = "auto", col = "auto")

table(PQ_R_avg_74$ever_74, PQ_R_avg_74$PD)

###########################
###########################
#DURATION Exposure Assessment
###########################
###########################

#create duration variables (ie count number of years in window lbs/year was >0)

#first create indicator that year's lbs PQ applied within buffer was >0
PQ_C_all_74$num<-ifelse(PQ_C_all_74$ChemPound_avg>0,1,0)
PQ_R_all_74$num<-ifelse(PQ_R_all_74$ChemPound_avg>0,1,0)

#create indicator to show the record had exposure assessment that year. will need to weight the duration by the total years in the period, which is potentially different by participant
PQ_C_all_74$ind<-1
PQ_R_all_74$ind<-1

#count number of years: Duration (number of years with PQ exposure) and Max (number of years with exposure assessment)
PQ_C_sum_74 <- PQ_C_all_74 %>%
  dplyr::group_by(PEGID) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(Duration = sum(num), Max=sum(ind))  

PQ_R_sum_74 <- PQ_R_all_74 %>%
  dplyr::group_by(PEGID) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(Duration = sum(num), Max=sum(ind))  

#now get the percent of years in period with exposure
PQ_C_sum_74$dur_percent_74<-PQ_C_sum_74$Duration/PQ_C_sum_74$Max
PQ_R_sum_74$dur_percent_74<-PQ_R_sum_74$Duration/PQ_R_sum_74$Max

#combined with covariates
PQ_C_sum_74<-merge(PQ_C_sum_74, C_cov, by='PEGID')
PQ_R_sum_74<-merge(PQ_R_sum_74, R_cov, by='PEGID')


########################
#get exposure assessment descriptives (for Table 2 descriptives)

PQ_R_sum_74 %>% group_by(PD) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(count=n(), mean=mean(dur_percent_74, na.rm=T), sd=sd(dur_percent_74, na.rm=T))
## # A tibble: 2  4
##      PD count  mean    sd
##   <int> <int> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1     0   821 0.188 0.244
## 2     1   824 0.232 0.280
PQ_R_sum_74 %>% dplyr::summarise(IQR=IQR(dur_percent_74, na.rm=T))
##         IQR
## 1 0.3333333
PQ_C_sum_74 %>% group_by(PD) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(count=n(), mean=mean(dur_percent_74, na.rm=T), sd=sd(dur_percent_74, na.rm=T))
## # A tibble: 2  4
##      PD count  mean    sd
##   <int> <int> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1     0   782 0.183 0.244
## 2     1   800 0.237 0.290
PQ_C_sum_74 %>% dplyr::summarise(IQR=IQR(dur_percent_74, na.rm=T))
##         IQR
## 1 0.3076923
#Supplemental Table 1 descriptives
PQ_R_sum_74 %>% dplyr::group_by(PD) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(count=n(), mean=mean(Max, na.rm=T), sd=sd(Max, na.rm=T))
## # A tibble: 2  4
##      PD count  mean    sd
##   <int> <int> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1     0   821  31.4  4.44
## 2     1   824  31.3  5.20
PQ_C_sum_74 %>% dplyr::group_by(PD) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(count=n(), mean=mean(Max, na.rm=T), sd=sd(Max, na.rm=T))
## # A tibble: 2  4
##      PD count  mean    sd
##   <int> <int> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1     0   782  23.9  9.28
## 2     1   800  27.1  9.02
########################
#scale per IQR
PQ_C_sum_74$dur_percent_IQR <- scale(PQ_C_sum_74$dur_percent_74, center = F, scale = IQR(PQ_C_sum_74$dur_percent_74, na.rm=T))
PQ_R_sum_74$dur_percent_IQR <- scale(PQ_R_sum_74$dur_percent_74, center = F, scale = IQR(PQ_R_sum_74$dur_percent_74, na.rm=T))

## Exposure assessment: 1974-index year with 10y lag
## Repeat steps for lagged time window

###########################
###########################
#AVERAGE INTENSITY Exposure Assessment
###########################
###########################


#include years prior to index year (PD diagnosis/interview) with 10 year lag for each participant
PQ_C_all_10l<-PQ_C_all_2[PQ_C_all_2$Year<PQ_C_all_2$IndexYR10, ]
PQ_R_all_10l<-PQ_R_all_2[PQ_R_all_2$Year<PQ_R_all_2$IndexYR10, ]

#average the ChemPound across years in the exposure window:
PQ_C_avg_10l <- PQ_C_all_10l %>%
  dplyr::group_by(PEGID) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(ChemPound_avg_10l = mean(ChemPound_avg))  

PQ_R_avg_10l <- PQ_R_all_10l %>%
  dplyr::group_by(PEGID) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(ChemPound_avg_10l = mean(ChemPound_avg))  

#combined with covariates
PQ_C_avg_10l<-merge(PQ_C_avg_10l, C_cov, by='PEGID')
PQ_R_avg_10l<-merge(PQ_R_avg_10l, R_cov, by='PEGID')


########################
#get average exposure assessment descriptives (for Table 2 descriptives)

PQ_R_avg_10l %>% group_by(PD) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(count=n(), mean=mean(ChemPound_avg_10l, na.rm=T), sd=sd(ChemPound_avg_10l, na.rm=T))

  dplyr::summarise(Duration = sum(num), Max=sum(ind))

  dplyr::group_by(PEGID) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(Duration = sum(num), Max=sum(ind))

#create indicator that record had GRAPES that year, ie there is a record here. will need to weight the duration by the total years in the period, which is different for everyone
PQ_C_all_20$ind<-1
PQ_R_all_20$ind<-1

#count number of years
PQ_C_sum_20 <- PQ_C_all_20 %>%
  dplyr::group_by(PEGID) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(Duration = sum(num), Max=sum(ind))  

PQ_R_sum_20 <- PQ_R_all_20 %>%
  dplyr::group_by(PEGID) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(Duration = sum(num), Max=sum(ind))

PQ_R_sum_20$dur_percent_20<-PQ_R_sum_20$Duration/PQ_R_sum_20$Max

PQ_R_sum_20<-merge(PQ_R_sum_20, R_cov, by='PEGID')

## 1974-index year

###########################
###########################
#Table 2 OR (95% CI)

#Function to output PQ model estimates

PQ_output <- function(m){
  cbind (OR  = exp(m$coefficients[2]),
         LCL = exp(confint(m)[2,1]),
         UCL = exp(confint(m)[2,2]),
         p = coef(summary(m))[2,4])
}

#######
#combine residence (R) and workplace (C) exposure estimates for RC model
Comb_RC<-merge(PQ_R_avg_10, PQ_C_avg_10[,c('PEGID','ever_10')],  by='PEGID')

m1<-glm(PD ~ ever_10.x + ever_10.y + agenew + factor(Race3) + Sex + IndexYR + Study, family=binomial, data=Comb_RC)

exp(m1$coefficients[2:3])#ORs
## ever_10.x ever_10.y 
## 1.4607583 0.9930366
exp(confint(m1)[2:3,c(1,2)])#95% CIs
## Waiting for profiling to be done...
##               2.5 %   97.5 %
## ever_10.x 1.1309474 1.889759
## ever_10.y 0.7585399 1.299778
coef(summary(m1))[2:3,4]#p-values
##   ever_10.x   ever_10.y 
## 0.003791334 0.959411883

# Correlation Between Exposure Assessments


#heatmap
# Get lower triangle of the correlation matrix
get_lower_tri<-function(cormat){
  cormat[upper.tri(cormat)] <- NA
  return(cormat)
}
# Get upper triangle of the correlation matrix
get_upper_tri <- function(cormat){
  cormat[lower.tri(cormat)]<- NA
  return(cormat)
}
reorder_cormat <- function(cormat){
  # Use correlation between variables as distance
  dd <- as.dist((1-cormat)/2)
  hc <- hclust(dd)
  cormat <-cormat[rev(hc$order),hc$order]
}


#######
#Residential Assessments
#######

#combined exposure variables into single dataset
PQ_R_exp<-merge(PQ_R_avg_74[, c('PEGID','ChemPound_avg_74','ever_74')], PQ_R_avg_10l[, c('PEGID','ChemPound_avg_10l','ever_10l')], by='PEGID', all=T)
PQ_R_exp<-merge(PQ_R_exp, PQ_R_avg_20[, c('PEGID','ChemPound_avg_20','ever_20')], by='PEGID', all=T)
PQ_R_exp<-merge(PQ_R_exp, PQ_R_avg_10[, c('PEGID','ChemPound_avg_10','ever_10')], by='PEGID', all=T)

PQ_R_exp<-merge(PQ_R_exp, PQ_R_sum_74[, c('PEGID','dur_percent_74')], by='PEGID', all=T)
PQ_R_exp<-merge(PQ_R_exp, PQ_R_sum_10l[, c('PEGID','dur_percent_10l')], by='PEGID', all=T)
PQ_R_exp<-merge(PQ_R_exp, PQ_R_sum_20[, c('PEGID','dur_percent_20')], by='PEGID', all=T)
PQ_R_exp<-merge(PQ_R_exp, PQ_R_sum_10[, c('PEGID','dur_percent_10')], by='PEGID', all=T)


#######
#Workplace Assessments
#######

#combined exposure variables into single dataset
PQ_C_exp<-merge(PQ_C_avg_74[, c('PEGID','ChemPound_avg_74','ever_74')], PQ_C_avg_10l[, c('PEGID','ChemPound_avg_10l','ever_10l')], by='PEGID', all=T)
PQ_C_exp<-merge(PQ_C_exp, PQ_C_avg_20[, c('PEGID','ChemPound_avg_20','ever_20')], by='PEGID', all=T)
PQ_C_exp<-merge(PQ_C_exp, PQ_C_avg_10[, c('PEGID','ChemPound_avg_10','ever_10')], by='PEGID', all=T)

PQ_C_exp<-merge(PQ_C_exp, PQ_C_sum_74[, c('PEGID','dur_percent_74')], by='PEGID', all=T)
PQ_C_exp<-merge(PQ_C_exp, PQ_C_sum_10l[, c('PEGID','dur_percent_10l')], by='PEGID', all=T)
PQ_C_exp<-merge(PQ_C_exp, PQ_C_sum_20[, c('PEGID','dur_percent_20')], by='PEGID', all=T)
PQ_C_exp<-merge(PQ_C_exp, PQ_C_sum_10[, c('PEGID','dur_percent_10')], by='PEGID', all=T)

#######
#Combined
#######

#add _R suffix to residential and _C for occupational
colnames(PQ_R_exp)[2:13]<-paste(colnames(PQ_R_exp)[2:13],"R",sep="_")
colnames(PQ_C_exp)[2:13]<-paste(colnames(PQ_C_exp)[2:13],"C",sep="_")

PQ_R_exp<-PQ_R_exp[PQ_R_exp$PEGID %in% PQ_C_exp$PEGID, ]
PQ_C_exp<-PQ_C_exp[PQ_C_exp$PEGID %in% PQ_R_exp$PEGID, ]

table(PQ_R_exp$PEGID==PQ_C_exp$PEGID)
## 
## TRUE 
## 1827
PQ_exp<-cbind(PQ_R_exp, PQ_C_exp)


#CLUSTERED BY DISTANCE
PQ_exp$PEGID<-NULL
PQ_exp<-data.frame(lapply(PQ_exp, function(x) as.numeric(as.character(x))))
PQ_exp$PEGID<-NULL

PQ_exp.cor <- cor(PQ_exp, use="pairwise.complete.obs")

cormat <- PQ_exp.cor

#order by distance
cormat <- reorder_cormat(cormat)

#met from data.table or reshape2!
melted_cormat <- melt(cormat, na.rm = TRUE)

#setup a new value that's only above 0.7
melted_cormat$value2<-ifelse(melted_cormat$value>0.25, round(melted_cormat$value,2)  ,NA)

myplot<-
  ggplot(data = melted_cormat, aes(Var2, Var1, fill = value))+ geom_tile() +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "blue", high = "red", mid = "white", space = "Lab", name="Pearson\nCorrelation") +
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = -45, vjust = 1, size = 11, hjust = 0))+
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(size = 11, hjust = 1)) +
  coord_fixed()+ ylab("")+xlab("")+
  scale_y_discrete(label = function(x) stringr::str_trunc(x, 35), position = "right") +
  scale_x_discrete(label = function(x) stringr::str_trunc(x, 25))+
  ggtitle("Paraquat Exposure Assessments ",subtitle ="Correlation Heatmap")+
  geom_text(aes(Var2, Var1, label = value2), color = "black", size = 1.75, na.rm = TRUE)+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 20), plot.subtitle =  element_text(size = 16))  + theme(legend.position="right")

  var = c("0:All",'1:Stratified','2:Additional Adjustment'),
  var_color = c("grey", "white", "white")
)

tp$strata <- "Primary Analysis"

dur_10$log_odds<-log(dur_10$OR)
dur_10$log_LCL<-log(dur_10$LCL)
dur_10$log_UCL<-log(dur_10$UCL)


p3.3<-ggplot(dur_10, aes(x = log_odds, y = reorder(strata,order) ))  +
  geom_errorbar(aes(xmin=log_LCL, xmax=log_UCL), width=.1, alpha=0.3) + 
  geom_vline(data=filter(dur_74, facet_x=="Residence"), aes(xintercept=log(1.67)), colour="grey40", linetype="dashed") + 
  geom_vline(data=filter(dur_74, facet_x=="Workplace"), aes(xintercept=log(1.86)), colour="grey40", linetype="dashed") + 
  geom_point(aes(color = log_odds), alpha = 0.90, size=3)  +
  theme_ipsum()   +
  xlab("Log Odds for PD") + ylab("")  + 
  geom_rect(data = subset(tp,facet_y == '0:All'),aes(fill = facet_y),xmin = -Inf,xmax = Inf, ymin = -Inf, ymax = Inf,alpha = 0.15) +
  facet_grid(facet_y~facet_x, scales = 'free_y', space='free_y',labeller = labeller(facet_y = c('0:All' = "","1:Stratified" = "Stratified Analyses" ,"2:Additional Adjustment" = "Additional\nAdjustments"))) + 
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, color = "grey40")  + 
  scale_color_viridis(name = "Log Odds", option="magma", direction=-1, limits = c(0, 1.5), guide = guide_legend(override.aes = list(color = "white"))) + 
  theme(legend.text = element_text(color = "white"),legend.title = element_text(color = "white")) + 
  theme(strip.text.y = element_text(size = 9)) +
  theme(panel.spacing = unit(0.75, "lines")) + ggtitle('10y prior to index year') +
  theme(plot.caption = element_text(hjust = 0, face= "italic"), plot.title.position = "plot", plot.caption.position =  "plot") + guides(fill='none') + xlim(-0.5,2.5) + theme(plot.margin = unit(c(-0.3,1,0.5,1), 'lines'))  + 
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, color = "grey40") 

#unit(c(top, right, bottom, left), units).

#Figure 3
ggarrange(p3.1, p3.2, p3.3, ncol = 1)

#combine residence (R) and workplace (C) exposure estimates for RC model
Comb_RC<-merge(PQ_R_avg_10l, PQ_C_avg_10l[,c('PEGID','ever_10l')],  by='PEGID')

m1<-glm(PD ~ ever_10l.x + ever_10l.y + agenew + factor(Race3) + Sex + IndexYR + Study, family=binomial, data=Comb_RC)

##   1.002557   1.281341

## dur_percent_10l 2.119394 1.288424 3.511346 0.00327758
#######
#combine residence (R) and workplace (C) exposure estimates for RC model
Comb_RC<-merge(PQ_R_sum_10l, PQ_C_sum_10l[,c('PEGID','dur_percent_10l')],  by='PEGID')

m1<-glm(PD ~ dur_percent_10l.x + dur_percent_10l.y + agenew + factor(Race3) + Sex + IndexYR + Study, family=binomial, data=Comb_RC)

exp(m1$coefficients[2:3])#ORs
## dur_percent_10l.x dur_percent_10l.y 
##          1.186754          1.840073
exp(confint(m1)[2:3,c(1,2)])#95% CIs
## Waiting for profiling to be done...
##                       2.5 %   97.5 %
## dur_percent_10l.x 0.7498468 1.878658
## dur_percent_10l.y 1.1702171 2.904643
coef(summary(m1))[2:3,4]#p-values
## dur_percent_10l.x dur_percent_10l.y 
##       0.464466823       0.008491404
